### Flowbase - sample requests
### Works with the VS Code "REST Client" extension, or copy the curl equivalents.
### Run `npm run seed` in /backend first so these slugs exist.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:4000

### 1. Log in to get a management token
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@orchestrator.dev",
  "password": "Admin@123"
}

### Expected response:
# {
#   "success": true,
#   "data": {
#     "token": "eyJhbGciOi...",
#     "user": { "id": "...", "email": "admin@orchestrator.dev", "role": "admin" }
#   }
# }


### 2. Verify a PAN - public endpoint, no auth
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/run/verify-pan
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "pan": "ABCDE1234F"
}

### Expected response:
# {
#   "success": true,
#   "requestId": "...",
#   "data": {
#     "valid": true,
#     "status": "VERIFIED",
#     "name_on_record": "RAVI KUMAR SHARMA",
#     "pan_masked": "XXXXXX234F"
#   }
# }


### 3. Same endpoint, invalid format -> 400 with validation details
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/run/verify-pan
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "pan": "not-a-pan"
}

### Expected response:
# {
#   "success": false,
#   "error": {
#     "message": "Validation failed",
#     "details": ["body.pan: \"pan\" with value \"not-a-pan\" fails to match the required pattern: ..."]
#   }
# }


### 4. Create an API key (requires the token from step 1)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/api-keys
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "label": "demo key"
}


### 5. Verify PAN then conditionally fetch GST - requires an API key
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/run/verify-pan-and-gst
Content-Type: application/json
X-API-Key: ok_your_key_here

{
  "pan": "ABCDE1234F"
}

### Expected response (abridged):
# {
#   "success": true,
#   "data": {
#     "pan_valid": true,
#     "gst_checked": "success",
#     "combined": { "gstin": "27ABCDE1234F1Z5", "business_name": "SHARMA TRADING CO.", ... }
#   }
# }


### 6. Document verification - runs OCR, then fraud check + face match in parallel
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/run/verify-document
Content-Type: application/json
X-API-Key: ok_your_key_here

{
  "image_base64": "base64-placeholder",
  "selfie_base64": "base64-placeholder"
}

### Expected response:
# {
#   "success": true,
#   "data": {
#     "extracted_name": "RAVI KUMAR SHARMA",
#     "fraud_flagged": false,
#     "face_match_score": 0.87,
#     "decision": "APPROVED"
#   },
#   "trace": [
#     { "stepId": "ocr", "type": "http", "status": "success", "durationMs": 320 },
#     { "stepId": "fraudCheck", "type": "http", "status": "success", "durationMs": 210 },
#     { "stepId": "faceMatch", "type": "http", "status": "success", "durationMs": 290 },
#     { "stepId": "parallelChecks", "type": "parallel", "status": "success", "durationMs": 291 },
#     { "stepId": "aggregateScore", "type": "transform", "status": "success", "durationMs": 0 },
#     { "stepId": "decision", "type": "transform", "status": "success", "durationMs": 0 }
#   ]
# }


### 7. Ask the AI agent to draft a new workflow from plain English
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/ai/generate
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "description": "Verify a PAN using Vendor A and, if it is valid, fetch GST details from Vendor B"
}


### 8. Metrics
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/metrics


### 9. Prometheus-format metrics
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/metrics/prometheus
